  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in Mississippi totaled $3.6B in FY2026 to date, with 66,726 awards and an average award size of $53.9K. Obligations fell 55.0% year over year. Historic annual totals show variability: FY21 was $4.9B, FY22 was $5B, FY23 was $8.7B, FY24 was $6.5B, and FY25 was $8B. The Department of Defense accounted for the largest share of FY2026 to date obligations at $3B. Ship Building and Repairing was the top industry by obligations at $2B. Other notable FY2026 to date agency obligations include National Aeronautics and Space Administration at $199M and Department of Veterans Affairs at $141M. Major vendors with significant FY2026 to date obligations include HUNTINGTON INGALLS INCORPORATED at $1.9B and VERTEX AEROSPACE LLC at $412M. The FY2026 to date profile reflects concentrated spending in defense-related vendors and industries alongside smaller obligations across civilian agencies such as Department of Commerce at $35.7M and Environmental Protection Agency at $17.3M.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What drove the year-over-year change in obligations?",
        "body": "Obligations fell 55.0% year over year, with FY2026 to date at $3.6B compared with FY25 at $8B. A large share of FY2026 to date obligations remained concentrated in the Department of Defense at $3B and in Ship Building and Repairing at $2B, indicating a shift in where remaining obligations are concentrated. The FY2026 to date total of $3.6B follows several higher annual totals in FY23 and FY25 of $8.7B and $8B respectively. Award volume remained substantial at 66,726 awards with an average award size of $53.9K."
      },
      {
        "heading": "How is FY2026 to date spending distributed across agencies and vendors?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense led FY2026 to date agency obligations at $3B, followed by National Aeronautics and Space Administration at $199M and Department of Veterans Affairs at $141M. HUNTINGTON INGALLS INCORPORATED was the largest vendor at $1.9B, and VERTEX AEROSPACE LLC was second at $412M. Top industries were led by Ship Building and Repairing at $2B and Other Support Activities for Air Transportation at $464M, with Facilities Support Services at $111M and Computer Systems Design Services at $45.5M rounding out notable sectors."
      }
    ]
  },
